reviews.text: Our tour guide was highly knowledgeable and great with kids! It was a pleasure to learn some amazing facts about this important building and our connection to Lincoln. Also about how marble patterns were artistically created on concrete over wood to keep the cost down.

This is the very place that me Steve Jolliff is not being heard as an American. They refuse to help and keep brushing off. I have no one in the world to turn to work a problem that negects all rights we have worked hard to explain as professionals. Idaho is the sickest state yet to abuse American rights.

Beautiful historical building definitely worth a visit. Start off in the basement level where there is an interesting exhibit of The Capital Building history, as well as some legislative history and education. There is also a free guide book for a self tour in the gift shop.

We took the group guided tour of the Capitol Building over the summer. Simply spectacular, the white marble has to be seen up close. Extraordinary place and fascinating history. Highly recommended to plan ahead to schedule a tour.

What a beautiful building. When we travel to new States, we like to stop at the Capitol Buildings. this one is absolutely gorgeous. You walk in and it's all white marble. Gorgeous White marble. 

There isn't a whole lot to see. On the garden view floor, there's a small area with some history and a little gift shop. 

on the 4th or 5th floor there's a couple of statues and you can look down in the center. there's meter parking all around. You probably won't spend more than an hour inside. There's no real Direction of where to go. There's no help desk or anything like that. 

Definitely worth a pop in just to look at the beautiful marble, if nothing else.

Great place to walk with your animals or kids. Scenery is awesome no matter the time of year.  If you love taking photos this is the place to go.  Plus it's  close to the train depot which is another great place to see and take photos at.

It's a lovely park, the grass definitely takes some abuse from all the events and festivals that use the space, but there are many beautiful large old trees growing throughout the park. Being so centrally located your are surrounded by other family attractions: the main library, the zoo, Anne Frank memorial, art museum, Rose garden, Discovery center, and the Boise river. To name a few.

I have to say that I don't think that there needs to be so many things that take place in the park. I do allot of volunteers work as well as donating allot of money and to Time worthwhile causes. I don't want to be hit up for donations to be able to use the park. I also don't want to be surrounded by who ever holding their function in the park

What do these Stars really mean? Rating is not always true but if it written right they out there only view in answer. The place is great until you study those who study. When do they wake up on the same side of knowing a path?

If you're looking a beautiful, calm place in Boise downtown to spent some time (or evening/morning walk) then Julia Davis Park is one of the option for you. I visited the park during my recent visit and I'd definitely like to visit it again if I ever come to Boise in future. Just wondering how the place look like in Winter!!

What a wonderful gift we have in this museum!  We came here with little expectations and we left here planning our next visit.  Our party ranged from 9 years old to 65, and everyone enjoyed the time exploring the museum.  There are a lot of interactive exhibits to really drive the history of our great state.  Take the time to check it out!

Idaho State Museum shows the history of Idaho in pictures, arts, and exhibits. I'm impressed by how they preserve the records of the past to let the young people see today what happened ages ago. There are also interactive rooms that keep us involved and enjoy our visit to the museum. I don't think I was able to see everything but I would like to go back another day to check everything.

Very well done little museum displaying lots of Idaho history. Everything was clean and working no problems with any of the displays. There was a whole playground area with lots of fun activities for kids to keep them interested. The display/movie for the big burn was impressive. The bathrooms were clean and well stocked. Overall I actually learned a lot despite being a local my whole life. I also really appreciated the respect that was shown to our Native American people in these works.

The remodeled museum is an absolute masterpiece! It is highly interactive and built in rooms that make it easy to manage groups of children. I went with a group of 4th graders and they were entertained for 2 hours. I felt proudly that it greatly represents our amazing state. It will easily impress visitors and locals. A must see!

Loved it and so did my 3 and 5 year old. They enjoyed the whole museum. Very organized and awesome for the small space. Just be aware it is tight in the exhibits so plan accordingly. We ditched our stroller half way through.

Interesting and informative. Quiet sitting place, great quotes. I know Ann Frank's story and it was required reading when I was in school. If you forget, you're doomed to repeat. Educational without being too descriptive or inappropriate (for all ages).

It is a good place to learn about Anne Frank and the Holocaust. It has a lot of information you can learn. If you go, obviously it is a place of respect, so you should limit talking to a tiny whisper and not touch things (except for the little boxes that tell you information). Finally, if you go, you should NOT BREAK OR DEFACE ANYTHING! But have fun learning things you might not have known if you hadn't gone!
Very educational. A must visit to fully understand the relationship between you and the world. Do not miss it.
Very nicely kept memorial area, a few too many sponsor names and confusion. But a nice place to see and think about history.
A good well designed place to reflect on your thoughts, learn a little history and just enjoy the sun. Right off the bike path and short walking distance to many parks, restaurants and the library

This zoo has come a long way since I was a kid.  They are currently remodeling to bring in new animals right now and making exhibits nicer.  I'm impressed with their continuous efforts to make the zoo bigger and better.

I love zoos!! This is a pretty well rounded zoo. I wish you could walk all the way thru without backtracking. My kiddos like the giraffe enclosure and of course monkeys. My daughter always wants to get dipping dots and we love em as well. I like that they allow you to vote of certain projects and the front entrance.

Wonderful place to be for adult and children Zoo has been accredited so they get rare animals plus they are expanding all the way back to the tennis courts at Julia Davis and bringing in some more . Endangered species. Sogo support Zoo Boise. Some animals in their enclosures would not survive on their own in the wild that is why they're in zoos and they're trying to help animals endangered for extinction to breed Zoo Boise is becoming one of the big zoos that help wildlife to prosper and to grow so our grandchildren can see them too. Education is the key so get down to the zoo Boise bring the children and learn all about some of some of Mother Nature's miracles

It was a nice zoo. There are larger Zoos in Portland and Seattle, but this one was easy to access, prices were lower, and the animals easier to see. The people working there were nice, and it had a nice general feel to it.

My family loves Zoo Boise. It is a little zoo but we really enjoy the small town feel of it. Their butterfly exhibit in the spring/summer is fantastic. Sometimes we just go for that alone. Prices are reasonable and I love that they have half price admission on Thursday. If you like being able to go to the zoo more than once a year I'd highly recommend getting the family zoo pass. My family of 6 pass only cost us $100. Which pays for itself after a few visits! Totally worth it!

Very interesting place. Good tour with lots of information. Our tour guide was well informed obviously quite interested in the details of it's history. The weapons museum is amazing. From ancient swords to Tommy guns and Gatling guns, they had more than you'd ever imagine. Our niece loved it.

This is a really, really neat place to visit. It's sort of a piece of "odd" history, because it shows how the jail system improved, but it's also a last thing you think of when visiting Idaho. The fact that it is there, extremely intact, and well maintained provides a wonderful learning and historic experience 

I highly recommend waiting for the tour guides though. Our tour guide specializes in learning about all of the escapes and escape attempts and knew all sorts of fascinating stories that truly made this a great tour.

This is a fun historical place to take the family. it is full of interesting information about the old prison and the people that spent time there and what they were in there for. it very neat to see the old cell blocks and how the inmates lived. great place for a weekend adventure.

Awesome historical site! Definitely worth the time for a visit. Make time for a guided tour if possible, but explore the areas outside the tour too! It was neat to see the records and information that have been kept to preserve this site as it is, and to learn about the lives of the people kept in this penitentiary.

I highly recommend the tour. Its included in the entry price. Place is awesome for kids and adults. I suggest to be dressed warm. Tour guide has answered all the questions and was very knowledgeable about the history and facts or the place. Very affordable
Very cool place to take the family. We did a tour here and the guide was wonderful. Very good with kids. Our family learned a lot and it sparked a new interest in geology for my kids!

Just FANTASTIC !!!  Incredible graphics in several different media*, they show the hills, Mountains, Valley's, plateaus and faults, in ways that reveal how Idaho came to be what it is today.  Rich in history, there is information on the early miners (including women miners), the incredible Wealth taken from the Earth's crust, even Earthquakes and how crust "movements" have changed the surrounding areas.  *In addition to a huge wall map that shows the state in bold 3D Relief, there is an Excellent touch-screen display that goes from an overview, down to incredible detail on each of the mining districts and individual mines (with great old pictures of the buildings, people and equipment they used).  The docents were very knowledgeable and great at sharing their wealth of knowledge !!!  All this and Free admission !!!!
I was excited to see that idaho has so many more gems stones then I knew about. What an amazing place to find, and I've lived here all my life!

Helicoprion = buzz saw shark. I had no idea that millions of years ago Idaho was home to this awesome looking creature. Seriously, it has a huge circular saw looking blade vertically in its mouth. Crazy vicious looking thing cut its prey clean in half!!  See it here along with all kinds of geology and mining information. Did I mention FREE!!! And a great affordable gift shop. Really cool sliced meteor display. Lots of interesting stuff here.
Fun place to study rocks
Loved my collegiate experience at BSU. I have an undergraduate as well as a graduate degree from Boise State. Top notch education & a great environment.

Graduated in Business Marketing and got a great job at an agency right out of college. Great preparation, professors that care, great outdoor opportunities, within a mile of downtown, and in one of the greatest up and coming cities in the world!

Boise State Univeristy is a nice college campus, with great landscaping. It is easy to navigate and has many activities and events that one can attend. The professors and great and the staff is helpful. It has a nice library and activity center. The University is home of the Broncos footbal team, and BSU is famous for their blue turf on the football field.  I recommend this University to locals and anyone looking for a nice college town type atmosphere.
BSU felt like home away home. The student community made my exchange experience unforgettable and the teachers were exceptional. I couldn't ask for more.
Really good quality buildings and food selections, really bad dorms, or at least the ones we saw were bad. Really really big with lots of busy streets

It was such an amazing experience for me and my students. Its not every day you get to see such magnificent creatures so up close and personal.

The tour guides were amazing.  As a teacher I have been on many different types of and these specific guides are in this for the birds and kids.  Their knowledge and patience was awe inspiring.  I will definitely be back with my family.  Many thanks for this wonderful experience!

Was a great place to spend the afternoon. Didn't get a chance to check out the library on site but will be back for that. There were 9 of us ranging from 9 years old to 64. There was something for everyone. The staff was friendly, courteous, and knowledgeable. The displays and shows were thoughtful and fun. Will be back!

A  very Interesting place to take the whole family to learn about birds of prey. My favourite the Condor recovery program that they are doing. Take your whole family and enjoy all they have to show you.

What a fun trip! This is a quick ride from downtown Boise, you can see lots of birds of prey that are not able to be released, learn about the intervention (and dedication) needed to preserve various species of birds of prey. They are currently working to breed and release the California Condor — amazing work! Absolutely stay for the bird of prey demonstration/talk; wish we could be her in the fall for the outdoor demonstration!

Amazing experience! Loved the visitor center with all the story telling and research areas. Incredible views on the way up, and very cool close-ups with some birds of prey. You can tell the staff are very passionate about their work, it makes for a great experience.
Loved my collegiate experience at BSU. I have an undergraduate as well as a graduate degree from Boise State. Top notch education & a great environment.

Graduated in Business Marketing and got a great job at an agency right out of college. Great preparation, professors that care, great outdoor opportunities, within a mile of downtown, and in one of the greatest up and coming cities in the world!

The professors and great and the staff is helpful. It has a nice library and activity center. I recommend this University to locals and anyone looking for a nice college town type atmosphere.

Really good quality buildings and food selections, really bad dorms, or at least the ones we saw were bad. Really really big with lots of busy streets
One of our favorite places. Great pizza and sandwiches.  We love sitting on the patio!
The atmosphere had a very rustic, DIY garage setting. Really enjoyed pizza while enjoying indoor balcony views. An excellent place to take the family.
This place is only alright, I wasn’t super impressed with the pizza (Mexican pizza was by far the best we tried) but I still give 4 stars for the vibe (sitting outside on the patio) and the beer.
Great place for sandwiches and salads as well as pizzas. Very unique and rustic atmosphere with plenty of space for big groups and families.
Great food great service. Nice atmosphere

The service is always as exceptional as the food at this diner. Even a simple sandwich is made and served with the satisfaction of the customer in mind. I visit Rocky's about once a year and am never disappointed.

Food is pretty good and I love the"bottomless fries" with my burger. The best part about Rockies though id the atmosphere. Chill diner with good, usually oldies, music. I live when they have their DJ here playing the music (Korean war vet). There's lots of different stuff to check out, guitars in the ceiling, planes, old photos. They make awesome malts and shakes. Definitely a place worth checking out.

Super fun place! It was my first time going but super fun group or first date place! Very retro and nice, food is good, really well priced too. Its a smidge run down, the parking lot is kindof hard to get into but those are my only negatives, it's a cool place
Food was pretty decent, average diner style! Great customer service and cool atmosphere. Good place to hang out and drink coffee. Echoeve was really sweet and a great hostess!
Nice big burgers. Very good. Clean place. Waitress on skates. Was a great server

The restaurant is beautiful and romantic. I love the huge stone fire place! We were there Valentine's weekend and saw a proposal. As for the food, I wasn't impressed. This was our first time there and I did not enjoy my meal. I had the halibut and it was very greasy and I couldn't even finish it. My husband tasted it and said it was awful too. He, on the other hand, had the lamb shank and loved it. I'd be willing to try the restaurant again but I would definitely order something different.

Excellent food! My favorite part was that I like trying something new and my husband is a meat-and-potatoes guy and their menu easily accommodated both of our appetites. I had buffalo and my husband had a New York strip. I need a few alterations, due to some allergies and they easily accommodated that, as well.

Food was delicious! Our server, Shari, knew so much about the history of the place, recommendations on menu items, & different seasonal events within walking distance from the restaurant. She was so observant for drink refills, when we had decided our order, actually finished with our 1st course, waiting for entrees, ready for desserts. And there was a very large group just a couple tables over that she was helping as well. She truly knows customer service and guest satisfaction! Iwill definitely be going back and asking to be seated in her section!!!
Mind blown! I had a fabulous birthday dinner here. The service was perfect and the food was divine. I will definitely be back!

Good food and the stake is always worth it. Well cooked and flavored. The Elk stake was a little dry but it is nice to have some more exotic and lean meats on a menu.  There is lots of seating but on weekends it is best to have a reservation.
Really really nice restaurant and good food. Unfortunately it's just not my favorite. It's not their fault, it's my own taste. I would suspect others would rate it at five stars though.

One of our favorite restaurants. The service is always friendly and professional, the food is authentic and delicious with noodles and sauces both handmade fresh daily. Excellent environment and location. Really can't say enough about what a great place this is. Make a reservation now for your next date night!
Food is delicious. Staff is professional and courteous. Bread is fresh and salad has good flavor. Highly recommend you pay them a visit.

Our favorite place in Boise to eat!  Food is always excellent and staff is wonderful.  We go for birthdays, family visiting and basically whenever we can.  Best kept secret in Boise...or maybe not.  You need to make reservations early.
Had a lovely dinner to celebrate a birthday. Service was prompt and friendly and I enjoyed the fresh, house made pasta. Nice wine selections and everyone liked the spumoni ice cream for dessert.

Service is horrible. It was $41 for 2 12" pizzas,  and they wanted to charge another buck for ranch. We waited for what seemed like forever for our food and then we never saw another server. Never got the waters we asked for,  tables weren't cleared.  We aren't coming back... Idaho Pizza is definitely the way to go.

If you are looking for ridiculous wait times and expensive pizza, then this is your place.  We waited an hour for our pizza and there was barely anyone in there.  You can get a cheaper meal at a fancy restaurant.  The pizza is pretty good and cool toppings but its not worth it in the end.  The gf pizza is good but not Celiac's safe.  I'm sick as I write this.  The owner is not very good at customer service either.  After my family spent $120 for pizza one night, he had the audacity to charge us an extra 75 cents when we asked for ranch later during the meal.  Go to another pizza place.

Don't let the Social Justice Warriors keep you from enjoying this wonderful food and fun atmosphere. The food is always amazing. We have eaten here several times and haven't had anything we didn't enjoy.  Our favorite is definitely the amazing house salad, the bubble bread, and the Elk Sausage pizza.  Highly recommended.
Pretty expensive and not particularly good! They had a wonderful dark on tap. Cheesecake was tasty. Did I mention the prices?
Hands down some of the best gourmet food in Boise. Fairly priced for what you're getting.

Just gotta say that, in my humble opinion, this is, with out a doubt, the best Thai restaurant in Boise. Their red curry with beef is excellent. The vegetables are crisp and colorful. The red curry has just the right amount of kick, not overpowering, nor understated. My favorite is the Pad Thai! We usually order the chicken and add prawns. So often the prawns can be completely overcooked and rubbery, but not here! They are PERFECTLY cooked.
It's definitely worth the drive from downtown... that is, if you want great Thai. :-)
Great food. Very authentic. Flavors were great with all the food I have had here. Very quick service. Lunch hour is their busiest time. Price is right on and very large portions.

I absolutely love their food! My favorite dishes are the basil fried rice and drunken noodle. Don't get me wrong their food is out of this world, but the last few times that I ordered the basil fried rice it has been a bit bland and dry. Every time I ordered it, it was delicious but now maybe their is a new chef? I don't know but I am still a regular because their food is the best! Definitely recommend.

Great little restaurant. Four of us went, and we all loved the amazing food. Our server, Jaa, was great! Very helpful with pronunciations, and knowing how spicy each dish would be. We did not have reservations, but were able to get in with less than five minutes wait, even though they were pretty busy with a large party coming in. The parking can be a little tight toward the back.

One of the best Thai food joints in Boise! I frequent this place and they've got friendly staff. Food is a little pricey though. Thai is always a great option when you have many vegetarian friends. I'd definitely suggest this place to friends!
